Defination : Clasloaders
            The Java ClassLoader is an integral part of the Java Runtime Environment (JRE)
            that dynamically loads Java classes into the Java Virtual Machine (JVM).

Types: 1)Bootstrap Class Loader
       2)Platform/Extension Class Loader
       3)System/Application Class Loader

1)Bootstrap Class Loader: At the top of the class loader hierarchy is the Bootstrap Class Loader.
                          It’s the root of the class loading system in Java.
        For Java 8 and earlier:
                        Responsible for loading core Java classes (like java.lang.*, java.util.*)
                        from <JAVA_HOME>/jre/lib.
        For Java 9 and later:
                        Loads core Java classes from the modular runtime image, typically in the
                        <JAVA_HOME>/lib/modules or <JAVA_HOME>/jmods directory. The mechanism is
                        integrated with the Java Platform Module System (JPMS).
        Unique Characteristics:
                        It’s important to note that the Bootstrap Class Loader is not a Java object,
                        unlike other class loaders. It’s implemented natively in the JVM for performance
                        and fundamental security reasons.

2)Platform Class Loader: Starting with Java 9,the Extension Class Loader has been replaced by the Platform Class Loader.

        Responsibility:
                    The Platform Class Loader loads classes from the standard library and any additional platform libraries,
                     ensuring they are accessible to application-level code without mixing them into the bootstrap classes.
        Behavior:
                   In the class loader hierarchy, the Platform Class Loader sits between the Bootstrap Class Loader and the
                   System (Application) Class Loader, following the same delegation principles: it first asks its parent,
                   and if the parent cannot load the class, it attempts to load it itself.

3)System/Application Class Loader
                                This is the class loader responsible for loading application-level classes from the classpath.

        Responsibility:
                     It loads classes from the system classpath, which can be set using the CLASSPATH environment variable,
                     the -classpath command-line option, or the classpath specified in a manifest file within a JAR.
        Behavior:
                    When a request to load a class is made, the System Class Loader delegates the request up the hierarchy.
                    If neither the Bootstrap nor the Platform (Extension in Java 8) Class Loader can fulfill the request,
                    the System Class Loader attempts to load the class.

